(2, 'project423', '<h4><span style=\"color:#008000\">Reviewer 1 :</span></h4>\n\n<p>A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>4.&nbsp;Good</p>\n\n<p>A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>4.&nbsp;Good</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\n\n<p>A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>4.&nbsp;Good</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\n\n<p>A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>4.&nbsp;Good</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>5.&nbsp;Excellent</p>\n\n<p>A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>1. The problem is clearly identified as being the non-availability of a indigenized (and original) battery of neurocognitive tests for dementia, sensitive to the earliest disease-related changes. 2.The main unmet challenge seems to be that there is currently no battery of neuropsychological tests for dementia for an Indian population, that accounts for educational and cultural factors. The main thrust of the project is to design such a battery of tests that is computerized, web-enabled and performance-tested. A rehabilitation module is also promised. These objectives appear to be feasible. 3.The proposed work is undoubtedly important, given the prevalence of (undiagnosed) mental health problems in the country. The proposers mention novel HCI methods, as well as novel secure storage methods (for patient data), but do not give any details at all, so it is difficult to assess whether there will in fact be significant innovation required to produce the deliverables. The main novelty resides in the existence of the deliverable itself, since, if successful, it will undoubtedly impact clinical practice positively. Validation will be carried out on the large base of patients at AIIMS. There is some overlap with the past work of the PI from AIIMS. The cited references from the literature are almost all more than ten years old. 4.The proposers write that the computerized neurocognitive battery to be developed &quot;would be a human simulator to a neuropsychologist&quot; but do not explain this sentence. Presumably, the battery can be run autonomously, generating a test result mimicking a certain dementia condition, which then has to be diagnosed by the neuropsychologist being trained. If this is the case, I would suggest that this be made explicit, perhaps as a deliverable (&quot;battery in simulator mode&quot;?). Project tasks are well distributed across the team members and are feasible. 5. No specific mention is made of plans to change or update IT or health curricula. Plans for PhD production and targets are generic. 6.Team members are well prepared and equipped to deal with the project tasks. However, given the geographical proximity of the teams, the semestral frequency of group meetings is rather low and I would suggest more frequent (bimonthly, at least) meetings. 7.The mentors are well matched to the scope of the project, having developed similar systems in the US and India and the foreign mentor has given a strong letter of support, showing commitment to the project. 8. Not much attention has been given to outreach (a &quot;small workshop&quot;, training of students and meetings with computer professionals are the only items mentioned). Suggestion: More emphasis on exposing medical students to IT concepts and, conversely, IT students to medical problems, in the context of the work proposed to be done.</p>\n\n<p>B1. Any major mismatches in the proposed line item costs with the proposed item/work, in the format: Budget-head-Institution: Remarks. Example: &lt;Manpower-IITX: Remarks&gt;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>None observed.</p>\n\n<p>B2. Any major equipment proposed for purchase that may be otherwise possible to share with others or is usable through outsourcing, without adversely affecting the work.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>No.</p>\n\n<p>B3. If any proposed major equipment is costing more than Rs. 2,50,000, and sharing/outsourcing is possible but not suggested in the proposal, then (i) do you know if that equipment is already available (particularly in India) where its sharing/outsourcing may be possible, and (ii) is it absolutely necessary for the project.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>No.</p>\n\n<p>C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>The project plans to fill an important gap in the area of neuropsychological testing in an Indian context, but appears to have been written in a hurry, so that full attention has not been given to all aspects being evaluated. Also, it will produce deliverables as a result of standard statistical and IT methods and no innovation in these areas is to be expected. These observations led to my classifying the project as borderline.</p>\n\n<p>C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>B.&nbsp;Borderline</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h4><span style=\"color:#008000\">Reviewer 2 :</span></h4>\n\n<p>A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\n\n<p>A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\n\n<p>A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>1.&nbsp;Rejection Quality</p>\n\n<p>A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>4.&nbsp;Good</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>4.&nbsp;Good</p>\n\n<p>A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>4.&nbsp;Good</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>1. What is the role of a neurosurgeon (PIN2b) in a study on development and assessment of cognitive battery?. Development of a computerised neurocognitive battery for early detection of disease-related changes is scientific in theory. However, there are other important issues to be borne in mind - Dementias need not only be disease-related. It is also part of normal ageing, and other factors like psychological and physiological constitution of a person also play a role in cognitive decline. There is also drug induced dementia. For eg, anticholinergics, anticonvulsants, antihistamines and even some antibiotics are known to cause chronic changes in the mental status of the patients.These issues are not considered in thsi proposal. Moreover, the basal cognitive levels also vary between individuals. The basal (control) cognitive level for each individual is necessary to assess the cognitive decline. The investigators should have taken cognisance of this and outline how they are planning to address it. These various issues have to be addressed and separated from the changes which are precursor for AD. There is no mention of any of these. Without addressing these basic problems, the cognitive battery developed will serve no purpose. Using cognitive batteries to assess the level of dementia once the disease is diagnosed is different and using it for early detection even before the disease has manifested is different. Unless there is a way to differentiate age, drug and disease-related changes, there could be the danger of a non-AD changes being misattributed to AD leading to false positives. A person identified as being prediposed to AD could be put on medicines!. Cognitive ability need not be related to literacy, as claimed by the investigators!. Rehabilitation of patients with cognitive decline is a huge challenge and a complex problem. Human participation plays a major and prime role. Technology may have a more limited role. 2. The unmet challenge mentioned is &#39;use of computerised cognitive rehabilitation in India&#39;. The investigators should mention unmet scientific rather than technological challenge. Human participation plays a major and prime role in rehabilitation. Technology only makes it easy. One can still use the technology and end up not being successful!. Objective 1 - there are already two neuropsychological assessment batteries developed in India, one in AIIMS, Delhi and the other in NIMHANS, Bangalore. What then is novel in the development proposed by the investigators?. There is no inclusion of dementia associated with normal ageing process and also drug-induced dementias. Objective 2 - objective 2 does not sound practically feasible. objective 3 - the focus seem to be on using technology rather than any new paradigm for rehabilitation. The latter should be the focus. If the aim is to computerise what is already available, there is no novelty in the study. How big is dementia a problem in India?. No statistics have been provided. 3. That the developed battery will help discriminate between various grades and types of dementias is a tall claim. The investigators have to be more realistic in their claims as to what their proposed study can achieve. Item 7.1 - When there are already cognitive batteries developed for the Indian population, why have those been ignored?. It would make more economical sense to add onto the available ones than reinventing the wheel with huge funding unless what the investigators are proposing is very different to the already existing ones for the Indian population. If this is so, then it has not been spelt out. Item 7.2 - The investigators say &#39;if found effective in identifying dementias&#39;!. What happens if not?. It would be a waste of public money!. Functional, neurochemical and molecular mechanisms would be required for differentiating the different dementias.Cognitive neuropsychological batteries may have a limited role given the many variables associaed with it. It is important to know the limitations of one&#39;s study. There is no information on overlap with the investigators&#39; past and / or ongoing work. LIN2 (CP) have 3 ongoing projects on similar lines in Indian population. No overlap with data acquisition for this study has been mentioned. 4. There is no clarity on how the data will be collected and also on match of roles of LINs and PINs with their expertise. For example, what is the role of neurosurgeon? Item 9 mentions Annexure 6. However, there is no mention of Annexures 1-5! ITEMS 10 AND 11 NOT FOUND IN THE MAIN PROPOSAL. But Annexure 1 refers to Item 10, which does not figure in the main proposal! Technical plan (Annexure 1) - The investigators have mentioned they will carry out extensive review of literature for assessment of batteries for dementia. The reviewer feels they should have already done it before submitting the proposal. Then on what basis have they identified unmet challenges in this area? Technical plan for objective 1 - The proposers are planning to take 15 healthy volunteers in the age group 40-90 years. There is a fundamental problem in this. Age related dementias could be inluded in this. No inclusion and exclusion criteria have been proposed. On what basis will these volunteers be considered healthy? These 15 volunteers are further subdivided into 5 categories with different education levels. How are the education levels defined? What is the criteria used for this?. There is no clarity on any of these points. 15 volunteers is too small a number for such studies. Moreover, LIN2 has extensive ongoing and past projects on cognitive batetries in Indian population. There must certainly be exisitng data on normal Indian population. Will they be used for this project?. What will be the overlap between these projects? If required, the investigators say, there will be a second pilot study with 50 healthy controls and 50 cases of dementia. What defines the &#39;if&#39;?. This is not addressed nor is how the healthy and patient selection will be carried out. What is the age group? Objective 2 - The proposers say they will attempt to use the batteries on 400 patients? Why attempt?. They should be clear about the numbers they will commit to?. Will 400 patients be done separately in each of the 3 centres or will they be divided between the 3 centres?. This is not clear. Objective 3 - There are a number of rehabilitation programs available for cognitive decline. Are there any new paradigms the proposers are going to include?. The impression given is that there is nothing new except computerisation of the paradigms. If the proposers intend new paradigm development, then they are silent on it. There is no mention of the inclusion and exclusion criteria for any of the objectives. 20 patients committed to for this objective is too less to draw definitive conclusions. It is not clear how the post rehabilitation improvement is going to be assessed. There are many methods (eg. MR techniques) available for objective assessment of the effects of rehabilitation. Why haven&#39;t the proposers thought of using these to study the effectiveness of their developed rehabiliation battery?. Both AIIMS and PGI Chandigarh have state of the art such facilities. 5. NOT PROVIDED BY THE INVESTIGATORS</p>\n\n<p>B1. Any major mismatches in the proposed line item costs with the proposed item/work, in the format: Budget-head-Institution: Remarks. Example: &lt;Manpower-IITX: Remarks&gt;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>IIIT Delhi - What is the role of the six interns (six), who would be there for only 2 months. What purpose will they serve?. Personnel asked for is in excess. They have asked for 7 RAs but no PhD students!. Why? Domestic travel (5 lakhs) - Except PGI Chandigarh, all the other institutes are in Delhi. Why would they require 5 lakhs for domestic travel? AIIMS Why travel allowance is asked under the consumable head? Why are two project coordinators required in Delhi - one for IIIT Delhi and the other for AIIMS, Delhi. One should suffice. Funding to the tune of 72 lakhs has been asked under &#39;travel&#39; head. When tele communication without meeting in person are possible these days (eg. skype meets and conference calls), travel allowance to the tune of 72 lakh rupees is redundant.</p>\n\n<p>B2. Any major equipment proposed for purchase that may be otherwise possible to share with others or is usable through outsourcing, without adversely affecting the work.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>No investigators have provided information on the facilities already available with them.</p>\n\n<p>B3. If any proposed major equipment is costing more than Rs. 2,50,000, and sharing/outsourcing is possible but not suggested in the proposal, then (i) do you know if that equipment is already available (particularly in India) where its sharing/outsourcing may be possible, and (ii) is it absolutely necessary for the project.</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>No investigators have provided information on the facilities already available with them.</p>\n\n<p>C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>ITRA may not be the right agency for such work. There is no innovation in this proposal. OTHER COMMENTS Page limit has been overshot CVs of 3 LINs and 3 PINs have not been provided! LIN2 (Dr. Nehra) has 3 ongoing projects on cognitive decline assessment in Indian context but has not mentioned anywhere what overlaps with the proposed study. There will definitely be overlap because the subject matter is the same. This proposer says she will be able to devout only 20% of her research time to this project but has asked for Rs. 183.11 lakhs fund! PIN2a is not working on any projects currently and yet can devote only 10% of his research time to this project. PIN2b should be removed. Not only will a neurosurgeon have much role in the proposed study but her cv also indicates she has no priori work experience in cognitive battery development or assessment. And she can devote only 20% of her research time to this project. The 2 coPIs (PIN2b) from PGI Chandigarh, a neurologist and a psychiatrist, who would actually be relevant for the proposed study have not provided their cvs. What % of their research time can they offer for this project if they do not have time to provide their cvs.</p>\n\n<p>C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>C.&nbsp;Not Recommended for Support</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '', '1'),
(3, 'project426', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"color:#008000\">Reviewer 1 :</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1: The broad objective of the project are very interesting and pertinent. A2: The project is very ambitious. It is not clear how the experimental data to accomplish many of the computer modelling objectives will be obtained. A3: The authors will be using established methods. But it would be a useful contribution to have a &lsquo;handy&rsquo; device for PD diagnosis based on the alpha-Syn interactions. I am less optimistic about the success and the contribution of the computer modelling of the basal-anglia-cerebellum networks. A4: Some of the deliverables such as novel early PD diagnosis could have a great clinical value. The PIs have sufficient expertise to deliver the key deliverables. A5: The PhD training program is very well laid out. A6: The PIs are experts in the experimental methods that will be used in this project. The computational neuroscientists have not published much on basal-ganglia and cerebellum models. Therefore, I suggest that there is a tighter interaction with the Basal-Ganglia modelling group at the IIT Chennai. A7: The two mentors are clinicians and they are well suited for the third objective. For the first and second objectives I suggest that the PIs include some academic researchers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B1. Any major mismatches in the proposed line item costs with the proposed item/work, in the format: Budget-head-Institution: Remarks. Example: &lt;Manpower-IITX: Remarks&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B1: There are 8 PhD positions for the IIT Mumbai, but from reading the objective 1 it is not clear how 8 non-overlapping PhD projects that will run in parallel could be specified.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B2. Any major equipment proposed for purchase that may be otherwise possible to share with others or is usable through outsourcing, without adversely affecting the work.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I cannot comment on this</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B3. If any proposed major equipment is costing more than Rs. 2,50,000, and sharing/outsourcing is possible but not suggested in the proposal, then (i) do you know if that equipment is already available (particularly in India) where its sharing/outsourcing may be possible, and (ii) is it absolutely necessary for the project.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I cannot comment on this</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The major problem with the project is that there is a very little interaction between the three main objectives. There is a small overlap between Objective 1 and Objective 2, but the deliverables form the Objective 1 will come too late for the modelling. Moreover, it is not clear how apha-syn effects on the dopamine and neuron excitability will be modelled. In general, the contribution of the computer modelling to the other two objectives (1, 3) is not very clear.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B.&nbsp;Borderline</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"color:#008000\">Reviewer 2&nbsp;:</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Has anyone ever performed alpha-Syn amyloid formation. Relevant papers are missing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B1. Any major mismatches in the proposed line item costs with the proposed item/work, in the format: Budget-head-Institution: Remarks. Example: &lt;Manpower-IITX: Remarks&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">-</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B2. Any major equipment proposed for purchase that may be otherwise possible to share with others or is usable through outsourcing, without adversely affecting the work.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">-</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B3. If any proposed major equipment is costing more than Rs. 2,50,000, and sharing/outsourcing is possible but not suggested in the proposal, then (i) do you know if that equipment is already available (particularly in India) where its sharing/outsourcing may be possible, and (ii) is it absolutely necessary for the project.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">-</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">-</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C.&nbsp;Not Recommended for Support</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"color:#008000\">Reviewer 3&nbsp;:</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">1. Too many problems have been identified. From diagnosing symptoms (diagnosis should be for the causative factors and not symptoms)to understanding the molecular mechanisms underlying pathogenesis, predicting prognosis to effective interventions in PD have been mentioned in the project. There is also a quantum leap to spinal and motor circuits. The team is also concerned about development of neuropsychological batteries and the pressing need to expand the use of high resolution imaging techniques (page 13). Each of these are areas warranting independent studies in themselves. 2. The many objectives don&#39;t connect to a single focus. The proposal should have a practically feasible and attainable set of objectives addressing some specific questions. Otherwise, this proposal will end up collecting huge and assorted data, which may not lead to any conclusion. One of the major conceptual problem being faced by Western medicine is its structural reductionistic approach. There is increasing consensus on this by a growing number of biomedical scientists. In such a scenario, the statement by the proposers that an effective cure for PD can be found using the structural understanding of alpha-Syn oligomers and fibrils, and their work focus seems way out of sync with current changing paradigm (Item 6 - page 12). Moreover, in their own words, studies to block alpha-Syn as a treatment method has not been successful. Then, why are they proposing it? Changes in ligomers and fibrils may not be specific to PD and AD. There should have been a discussion on other neurological disorders where similar changes are seen and these should also be studied. Otherwise, the proposers will come up with a set of non-specific markers for PD. Objective 3 mentions study of animal model of PD. This will be a pre-clinical and not clinical study. Is the high resolution imaging for detecting PD on animals or patients?. This is not clear. Each objective has a number of points. Put together, there are 12 specific objectives. May not be feasible to carry out all these. Some of the objectives are disconnected as well. 3. There is no novelty in the work. The generated data will only supplement the existing data (according to the proposers themselves). What the proposers mean by &#39;All-atom molecular dynamics simulations&#39; is not clear. Using the data generated at the molecular level, the proposers say they can develop a device which is handy, label-free, limited processing of samples (what are these samples?) and quick response. These are tall claims. Without understanding the causative factors, only diagnosis of symptoms are possible. There are a number of imaging and other markers for such diagnosis. A few more markers (without knowing whether they are the cause or effect) will not solve the problem. The question remains whether alpha-Syn aggregation is a cause or effect. This fundamental question needs to be addressed. Page 15 - The proposers say their study will bridge the gap between physiological and pharmacological conditions in rats, humans and also growing diffusion of robotic devices in neuro-rehabilitation!. Caution is to be exercised when extrapolating data from animal studies to humans. This is more so in diseases like PD where there is extensive cognitive decline. So to say that their proposed study will connect points across different domains sounds too enthusiastic and not scientifically tenable. No information on past and ongoing projects and areas of overlap! 4. Dr. Sangeeta Rawat is a neurologist and not a radiologist. (It is not clear whetehr she is a mentor or a PIN). Radiologists perform scans. Infact usually it is the radiographers who perform the MRI scans. Radiologists interpret the scans. Neurologists definitely are not trained to perform imaging scans.It is not clear whether the high resolution imaging is using MRI. Dr. Shilpa Shanke&#39;s cv gives her address as Department of Neurology. But the proposal (page 7) mentions her department as Radiology. Her highest degree is MBBS. She is neither a neurologist nor a radiologist. Who will then do the MRIs?. There is no radiologist in the team!. Who will be the neurologist handling the PD patients?. There is no neurologist as well in the team, if Dr. Rawat is actually only a mentor. Development of cognitive battery does not gel with the rest of the objectives dealing with molecular structure determination and animal model PD. Infact, this objective should be dropped. There are other groups which have also proposed development of cognitive batteries. Objective 3, activity 1 - One of the aim of the project is to understand why aggregation occurs in alpha-Syn and identify the most potent neurotoxic species in alpha-Syn aggregation pathway (This will be used to induce PD in animals. This is different compared to the chemically induced PD in animals). This objective will be accomplished at the end of the 3rd year of the project (Page 18 - Year 3 in the first section). The structural study of these proteins will also reach its logistical conclusion only at the end of the 3rd year (page 18). Both these inputs are necessary to produce PD in animal models. The team on animal models hence will have to wait for the completion of the project to start their work on animals!. But, they don&#39;t seem to. They start their work from Year 1 onwards (Page 22). They reach their conclusion by the third year. There seems to be a complete mismatch in timing of the studies. Objective 3, activity 2 - Development of cognitive batteries should be removed. It does not gel with the rest of the objectives. Objective 3, activity 3 - There is already information on imaging data in PD patients. Imaging data repositories are available in public domain. So, there is nothing new that is going to be added. KEM Hospital, Mumbai where the concerned PIs are located should also have its data repository on PD patients. This activity will provide only be additional data input, which anyway may be part of KEM&#39;s diagnostic imaging routines. Technical plan - This is a section for outlining the technical details of the study. Instead, most of the sections have discussions on the aims and usefulness of the study. For example, objective 1c - no technical details are provided.Same with objectives 2a-2d and objective 3. Objective 3b again is a monologue on neuro-cognitive underpinning of PD. There is no technical plan provided. Objective 3c - again, there is no technical plan provided.What are the inclusion and exclusion criteria? Are all the patients going to undergo MRI and TRODAT?. If TRODAT (Technitium based Dopamine Transporter SPECT Imaging) scan is going to be, then why no coPI from Department of Nuclear Medicine since this study will have to be done in Nuclear Medicine?. Which MR and SPEC scanners are going to be used? What are the acquisition parameters. It is mentioned that MRI/TRODAT scans will be taken at the beginning of the enrolment and the second scan will be taken after 2 years.Will these patients be undergoing treatment during this intervening period?. No study plan seems to be in place. MRI can only document changes. It will not help understand progression of the disease. There seems to be no technical plan in place. 5. Targets across teams - There is no synchronisation of activities and the objectives are all not completely connected with each other. Going through the proposal, one gets a picture of all the LINs and PINs planning the proposal in isolation of their areas of expertise. Individual thoughts and plans are in place but no integration of these can be seen to aim for a specific goal. Page 28 - sudden mention of Prof. VS Chakravarthy, IIT Madras as a collaborator! 7.Dr. Sangeeta Rawat who is listed as a LIN (page 7) is also listed as a mentor (page 31)!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B1. Any major mismatches in the proposed line item costs with the proposed item/work, in the format: Budget-head-Institution: Remarks. Example: &lt;Manpower-IITX: Remarks&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">IIT Mumbai The budget in general seems very hyped. Equipments worth 100 lakhs have been asked. Instruments like fluorimeter, dynamic light scattering Instrument, Real time PCR, nanodrop, computer clusters and UPS should be available in IIT Mumbai. The investigators have to produce certificate from the Institute head that no department in IIT Mumbai has these equipments. They should also be asked to give a declaration that none of these equipments are available anywhere(including their collaborating Institutes)in Mumbai. On page 27 of the proposal, requirement for 8 PhD students is mentioned.On page 95 though, request is made for only 6 PhD students. Why is this discrepancy? Amrita Institute Rs. 10 lakhs have been asked for equipments. But there is no mention of what equipments are required. Similar presentation for stationery - they have asked for 0.30 lakhs but no mention of the items. Rs. 26.28 lakhs have been asked for manpower but no details given. This is repeated for all budget heads. A total of 14 PhD students for the study seems on the higher side.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B2. Any major equipment proposed for purchase that may be otherwise possible to share with others or is usable through outsourcing, without adversely affecting the work.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">No information on facilities available in the respective Institutes have been provided.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B3. If any proposed major equipment is costing more than Rs. 2,50,000, and sharing/outsourcing is possible but not suggested in the proposal, then (i) do you know if that equipment is already available (particularly in India) where its sharing/outsourcing may be possible, and (ii) is it absolutely necessary for the project.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The investigators have to produce certificate from the Institute head that no departments in their Institute has these equipments. They should also be asked to give a declaration that none of these equipments are available in any other institutions in their city(including their collaborating Institutes).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is a very ambitious and impractical proposal. There is no integration of ideas from the LINs and PINs. All of them will be acquiring data in their own sphere of expertise, which is ok. But no thought seems to have gone in as to how these information are going to be integrated to address specific questions. The proposal has overshot the page limit LINs and PINs - there seems to be confusion between who are the LINs and PINS. Pages 6 &amp; 7 mention Dr. Mohan Raghavan and Dr. Shilpa Shanke as PINS 1a and 1c. Page 7 mentions Dr. Mohan Raghavan as LIN1. And in this list (pages 7-9), there is no mention of Dr. Shilpa Shanke! Similar discrepancies are seen for other LINs and PINs Dr. Sangeeta Rawat is both a LIN and a mentor! Dr. Shilpa Shanke&#39;s cv gives her address as Department of Neurology. But the proposal (page 7) mentions her department as Radiology. Her highest degree is MBBS. She is neither a neurologist nor a radiologist. Who will then do the MRIs?. There is no radiologist in the team!. Who will be the neurologist handling the PD patients?. There is no neurologist as well in the team, if Dr. Rawat is actually only a mentor. None of the investigators have given complete details of their past and ongoing projects and areas of overlap. For example, Dr. Samir Maji&#39;s 2 of the 5 projects are alpha-syn related. There definitely are areas of overlap. But, he is completely silent about these. No project details have been provided by Dr. Rohit Manchanda and Dr. Shilpa. It is not clear whether they have never been involved in any projects or they have forgotten to provide. Dr. Sadhana Sathaye has no prior experience in PD models of animals. This is true of some of the other investigators as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C.&nbsp;Not Recommended for Support</p>\r\n', '', '1');
INSERT INTO `husmin_old_reviews` (`id`, `priject_title`, `reviewdata`, `by_whome`, `review_count`) VALUES
(4, 'project427', '<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#008000\"><strong>Reviewer 1 :&nbsp;</strong></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">NONE OF THESE COMMENTS MUST BE HIDDEN FROM THE AUTHORS OF THE PROPOSAL This is a multi-institutional effort to understand the feasibility of early detection of Alzheimer&rsquo;s Disease (AD) by studying progression of various traits and markers &ndash; clinical, neurocognitive, neuroimaging, genomic, epigenomic, biochemical, etc. &ndash; in three subgroups of individuals (normal, mild cognitive impairment [MCI], and AD) with data being collected at two time points during a 3-year period. This project will also create a centralized database of clinical, molecular and imaging data. The project seeks to address an extremely important problem that is of global importance. The set of institutions and investigators are extremely competent to carry out the proposed work. The methodology suggested is very appropriate. I shall strongly recommend that such a proposal be eventually supported. However, the investigators need to think through and document many details of the study, because in their enthusiasm to solve an important problem, they have addressed overarching issues, but have missed many details. Without trying to be exhaustive, let me be indicative of what I believe are shortcomings of the present proposal. The group of investigators are experienced and will be able to take cues from these indications and resubmit an improved version of the proposal for funding. (1) I think the investigators should have a model in their mind. This doesn&rsquo;t come through well. To generate a huge mass of multi-dimensional data on various constructs from each individual and then to imagine that a model can be extracted is not a convincing proposition. This is especially true because the sample size of each of the two patient subgroups is 35 and that of the normal subgroups is 60. (Incidentally, I am absolutely certain, in view of what I know about variability of some biochemical parameters among AD patients, the statement on page 34 &ldquo;The sample size was based on power calculation for two sample t-test using the conservative p-value 0.05 and power 0.8&rdquo; cannot be correct. I will, however, not hold the small sample sizes against the authors since generation of appropriate multi-dimensional data on each patient is expensive, and therefore necessarily pilot studies as the present one are required. May I request the authors to study the following two papers in which the authors have proposed and validated some models of AD, albeit focused on a specific set of putative markers: Jack CR, Jr, Knopman DS, Jagust WJ, et al. Hypothetical model of dynamic biomarkers of the Alzheimer&rsquo;s pathological cascade. Lancet Neurol. 2010; 9:119&ndash;128. Same authors: Update on hypothetical model of Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease biomarkers. Lancet Neurol. 2013; 12: 207&ndash;216. (2) Details of methodology are missing in most components. These include, but are not exhaustive, (a) patient and &ldquo;normal&rdquo; inclusion and exclusion criteria, (b) methodology of carrying out an integrated analysis of the multi-dimensional data [it is not sufficient to state that novel machine-learning tools will be developed, although I have no doubt that the ISI investigators are capable of doing this], (c) NGS methodology, etc. (3) Some aspects have not been thought through well. For example, is it appropriate to study microRNAs or epigenomics in the blood? What are the data-sharing protocols? (4) There is no governance or oversight protocol proposed, which is important for all multi-institutional projects. (5) The protocol of interaction among the institutions is poorly written.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Recommended for support, with extensive revision</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A.&nbsp;Recommended for Support</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#008000\"><strong>Reviewer 2 :&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">5.&nbsp;Excellent</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">5.&nbsp;Excellent</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">5.&nbsp;Excellent</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">5.&nbsp;Excellent</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A.&nbsp;Recommended for Support</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#008000\"><strong>Reviewer 3 :&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Fig 1 work flow is very busy and not clear. For neuroimaging biomarker to accurately predict disease progression more papers need to be cited.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B1. Any major mismatches in the proposed line item costs with the proposed item/work, in the format: Budget-head-Institution: Remarks. Example: &lt;Manpower-IITX: Remarks&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The novelty and application of the outcome has not been highlighted in detail as per funds proposed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B2. Any major equipment proposed for purchase that may be otherwise possible to share with others or is usable through outsourcing, without adversely affecting the work.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">-</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B3. If any proposed major equipment is costing more than Rs. 2,50,000, and sharing/outsourcing is possible but not suggested in the proposal, then (i) do you know if that equipment is already available (particularly in India) where its sharing/outsourcing may be possible, and (ii) is it absolutely necessary for the project.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">-</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Application of the outcome technology with such high budget proposed should be extremely clear.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C.&nbsp;Not Recommended for Support</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#008000\"><strong>Reviewer 4&nbsp;:&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The proposal seems well thought out and could be potentially useful in better understanding Alzheimer&#39;s disease. However, the proposal is primarily for a data collection and modeling project, and there is no specific proposal for an in silico simulator, except to say that one is &quot;eventually planned&quot;. Consequently, I cannot comment on this aspect. I do not have the requisite background to comment on the design of the planned cohort study, although it looks quite reasonable to me. Worthy of support in general, but perhaps not if a human simulator is a primary goal, as the path to such a simulator through this project is not clear.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B.&nbsp;Borderline</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">MIsc&nbsp;Text(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The proposal seems well thought out and could be potentially useful in better understanding Alzheimer&#39;s disease. However, the proposal is primarily for a data collection and modeling project, and there is no specific proposal for an in silico simulator, except to say that one is &quot;eventually planned&quot;. Consequently, I cannot comment on this aspect. I do not have the requisite background to comment on the design of the planned cohort study, although it looks quite reasonable to me. Worthy of support in general, but perhaps not if a human simulator is a primary goal, as the path to such a simulator through this project is not clear.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#008000\"><strong>Reviewer 5&nbsp;:&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The project is primarily aimed to facilitate early diagnosis of Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease (AD). The investigators propose to identify novel non-invasive imaging biomarkers along with clinic-biological tests, genetic, biophysical and biochemical markers for accurate and early diagnosis of AD and assess the prognostic value of these parameters. The hypothesis is good, however, the proposal is not specific and fails to clearly define realistic goals and expected outcome at the end of the 3 year project and needs to be extensively revised and rebudgeted. The following points should be addressed while revising the project: 1. The investigators highlight the need to develop novel neuropsychological markers of early AD in Indian population. It is rationalized that the existing markers are based on the Western population. 2. In order to address this at the national level as proposed , it is important to evaluate early AD patients from different geographical regions of the country due to the extensive diversity in the Indian population and not just from one city (Kolkatta). 3. Recruitment of only 35 early MCI cases and further follow up of limited subjects from this cohort may not generate any conclusive data. 4. For assessment of early soluble oligomers and aggregation of amyloid proteins, animal model study will be most appropriate. 5. For development of a mobile application suitable for Indian patients, a large number of patients from different regions of the country should be studied for the proposed parameters. 6. The approach that will be adopted to monitor early events of aggregation in vitro, in neuronal cell lines and in patient samples should be described in detail and preliminary supportive data should be furnished. 7. The MCI and AD patients should be age matched to avoid other confounding variables. 8. Unless MCI patients are followed up in adequate numbers, it will not be feasible to monitor late events of amyloid beta aggregation in patient samples.The same holds true to obtain Raman signatures from different stages of AD. 9. A longitudinal systematic study on a large number of MCI and AD patients from diverse regions of India will be required to analyze and correlate imaging data, biochemical, biophysical and genetic information in order to arrive at an integrative quantitative model and construct a computational biology/signaling pathway platform and further delineate alterations of the model by drugs and their toxicities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Validity of the hypothesis and its relation to specific targets: The hypothesis is good and will enable establishement of punch skin biopsy technique to diagnose small fibre neuropathies for the first time in India Proposed work plan a. How appropriate to the objectives? Well formulated b. Supporting elements (Infrastructure facilities, available expertise with the PI, etc.): Required facility is available with PI c. Hindering elements (Factors that may impede progress): None d. Alternate strategies (Whether the PI has an alternate strategy in case the proposed work plan fails). The proposed work plan is fool proof e. Synergy and complementarity of participating institutions and investigators (in case of inter-institutional projects): NA 8. Relevance and Applicability: Highly relavant and will help in diagnosis of such cases</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A.&nbsp;Recommended for Support</p>\r\n', '', '1'),
