n: justify;\">C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The project needs careful rewriting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C.&nbsp;Not Recommended for Support</p>\r\n', '', '1'),
(9, 'project451', '<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#008000\"><strong>Reviewer 1 :</strong></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">1. The biological/medical issue is clear, but the role and need of using conventional CFD is not clear. 2. The motivation and objectives of the proposed project are clearly defined - perhaps a bit too ambitious. 3. The researchers continually refer to high fidelity CFD, but they do not define nor clarify just how this is to be achieved, nor any discussion of the technical approach. The project deals with a huge multi-scale problem ranging from the micro-level (and chemical interactions) to the more macro-level associated with CFD. In order words, conventional CFD techniques are not going to be applicable if the range is to include the smallest levels of activity to the flow of blood and associated transport of chemicals. 4. The project appears to be bifurcated between the bio-science group and their appropriate micro-scales of research and the larger-scale, CFD efforts. There is a huge gap between these two regions of the project, and this gap is where much of the unknown occurs - and lack of procedures. 5. If the researchers pull this off, this would have a sizable impact on the curricula associated with both the biomedical as well as fluid dynamics fields. The ability to successfully model a wide range of multi-scale processes is one of the grand challenges of the scientific community, let alone the technical issues required for utilizing high performance computers (which will be needed). 6. The team appears to be well-qualified in their respective areas - the interesting aspect of this proposed project is knowing what to do to over the range of scales - and finding the expects (if they even exist) to handle this regime. 7. Finding and utilizing mentors is delicate here in that the biomedical and the fluid dynamics researchers are clearly capable and experienced, but it is not clear as to whom would be mentoring whom. 8. While I am sure there would be able outreach and dissemination of knowledge upon success of the project (and interim steps), the extreme technical difficulties attributed to understanding the biomedical as well as mathematical and computational rigors associated with CFD will become cumbersome to the lay person.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B1. Any major mismatches in the proposed line item costs with the proposed item/work, in the format: Budget-head-Institution: Remarks. Example: &lt;Manpower-IITX: Remarks&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I did not see any appreciable issues that were problematic with the proposed line item costs or proposed budgets. The fact that the project is aimed at a 3 year time frame may be a bit optimistic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B2. Any major equipment proposed for purchase that may be otherwise possible to share with others or is usable through outsourcing, without adversely affecting the work.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The biomedical equipment and resources for conducting human trial testing may be a bit underestimated. The purchase of a CFD package is typically a one time expense, with minimal annual maintenance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B3. If any proposed major equipment is costing more than Rs. 2,50,000, and sharing/outsourcing is possible but not suggested in the proposal, then (i) do you know if that equipment is already available (particularly in India) where its sharing/outsourcing may be possible, and (ii) is it absolutely necessary for the project.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I did not see any issue here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The proposed project is ambitious, especially to achieve success within a 3 year time period. Most medically-related projects generally last for many years, with escalating costs. Milestones and a detailed statement of work, with more in-depth discussion of the modeling aspects, would be helpful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B.&nbsp;Borderline</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#008000\"><strong>Reviewer 2 :</strong></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: just