rehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>This project aims to develop tools that can predict selected protein properties, and the propensity of proteins to misfold and aggregate under different conditions, such as pH, ionic strength, temperature, protein concentration, etc. The investigators propose to develop a prediction tool that can estimate protein properties, such as solubility, from knowledge of the sequence and conditions such as pH and temperature. The study will focus on majorly two proteins p53 and synuclein. A second aim of this project is to try and predict the propensity of nephrotic syndrome patients to suffer a relapse. The investigators propose to collect clinical data from patients with nephrotic syndrome. Kidney biopsy would be done in all these patients for histological characterisation. Also their sera, baseline and in limited follow up, would be subjected to proteomic and metabolomic analysis. It is intended to make use of machine learning techniques to develop a mathematical model to predict relapse of nephrotic syndrome. The objectives of the project are: 1. Develop input dataset of protein aggregation by varying solution conditions. 2. Predict intrinsic disorder content, and protein aggregation propensity. 3. Use data from nephrotic syndrome patients to predict the propensity to relapse. 4. Develop feature selection and classification methodologies to yield state of the art predictions, and to tune these methods for the application at hand. Comments: 1. The two aims of this project are relevant yet independent (no link) and actually are separate proposals. 2. In aim 1, the investigators propose to first identify, then define the role of predicted hot spots on the aggregation propensity of intrinsically disordered proteins. The investigators must specify and elaborate (detailed methodology on ) how this role will be elucidated and authenticated? 3. Further it is aimed to generate a tool for predicting protein properties from sequence and information on the environment (pH, temperature, etc.) that is proposed to be of use not only for the problem at hand, but for protein disorders in general, and for many medical applications. Can information generated from analysis of 2 proteins be generalized for different proteins and different disorders? While such tools are available at present, the project would attempt to beat the state of the art in terms of prediction accuracy. Provide specific details of what approach will be adopted for this purpose. 4. Furnish detailed methodology how this study will identify the initial trigger for aggregation. 5. A second aim of this project is to try and predict the propensity of nephrotic syndrome patients to suffer a relapse. It is intended to make use of machine learning techniques to develop a mathematical model to predict relapse of nephrotic syndrome The inclusion and exclusion crtiteria of patients with nephrotic syndrome should be defined; exact no. number patients to be evaluated in the two defined categories based on which budget should be appropriately defined.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>C.&nbsp;Not Recommended for Support</p>\r\n', '', '1'),
