(14, 'project463', '<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"color:#008000\">Reviewer 1 :</span></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">1.&nbsp;Rejection Quality</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">1.&nbsp;Rejection Quality</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This proposal state as and I quote &quot;Amyloid deposition is one of the prerequisites of Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease (AD) diagnosis. Pathogenesis of AD is still not fully understood. This is scientifically wrong statement. Clinical research shows that people even at the age of 88 have huge amyloid load factor (proven from their autopsy) were cognitively perfect and no AD or no MCI. The entire proposal is based on assumption due to lack of literature search and analysis. Having phosphorylated tau is the prerequisite for AD. Structural imaging (quantifying atrophy) based on magnetic resonance (MR) is an integral part of AD clinical assessment. In OPD , AD patients are being diagnosed by the following: neurological evaluation, neuropsychological test, gait exam. and CT scan is required. if required, PET scan can be used for validation for hyper or hypo metabolism. This is more than sufficient for the process. However, MRI is sometime required as it is cheaper than PET. Again it is written that &quot;However, high specificity required to minimize false-positive rate is lacking presently in MR image analytics. It can be partly attributed to the absence of correlation between biochemical and structural markers of AD.&quot; If it is found in clinical research available in huge data base (pubmed) That changes in the brain and biochemical profiles in the brain are pretty much being done and excellent correlation are obtained. scientist are doing the work in AD and then trying to look those changes in MCI and PRE-MCI. This is the theme of the research around the world. I sincerely request to get in touch with at least four journals: Journal of Alzheimer research, Alzheimer &amp; Dementia, Current AD research, Biological psychiatry, Neurology. it is proposed to have brain template and I quote &quot;In this project we propose to create a database of brain MR images for normal and AD subjects. &quot; There is a history of human brain template formation. In the literature please see we have still not published (Indian and African brain template) Chinese Brain Template(2010) French Brain Template (2009) Korean Brain Template (2005) ICBM-452 Brain Template (2003) MNI-152 Brain Template(2001) MNI-305 Brain Template(1995) Talairach and Tournoux(1957, 1967, 1988) I am optimistic in any of this places NIMHANS, AIIMS, NBRC or Nizam (Hyderabad) must be doing this and it is advised to look at those places I was hoping that a plan would have provided how to make brain template, simple maneuvering with registration will not do the job. One need specific way data collection and people do it for normal healthy aged person. Having brain template is not a simple word as it is too complicated as all brains have to be similar severity otherwise it can not be used at all. It was expected a real plan which is based on literature survey and also looking for the same task (if within India it is being done) -------------- in this proposal it is mentioned that &quot;The project will also consider in developing novel image processing algorithms for segmentation, registration and feature extraction.&quot; Thanks to contribution is various laboratory involved in AD research, image processing, segmentation and registration is highly enriched and there packages are easily available free of cost. I want to tell you that FREESurfer. what a excellent outcome and many leading scientists are using these package ( it is free and fantastic) <a href=\"http://freesurfer.net/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://freesurfer.net/</a> it is said &quot;We will perform FTIR and NMR spectroscopy for identifying the serum biomarkers. Identification of serum markers by metabolomics approach will lead the way for minimally invasive screeners of AD&quot; Please note at this stage blood peripheral system is affected much later stage than certain specific changes are seen as biomarker in the brain. this approach will help to identify early diagnostic marker for AD. It may be noted that atrophy is considered as important feature which is also seen in healthy aging, dementia in lewy body disease and FTD cases. So for differential diagnosis cases, one need to look beyond and literature search and analysis is required in depth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B1. Any major mismatches in the proposed line item costs with the proposed item/work, in the format: Budget-head-Institution: Remarks. Example: &lt;Manpower-IITX: Remarks&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">no comment</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B2. Any major equipment proposed for purchase that may be otherwise possible to share with others or is usable through outsourcing, without adversely affecting the work.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">no comment</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B3. If any proposed major equipment is costing more than Rs. 2,50,000, and sharing/outsourcing is possible but not suggested in the proposal, then (i) do you know if that equipment is already available (particularly in India) where its sharing/outsourcing may be possible, and (ii) is it absolutely necessary for the project.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">no comment</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This proposal was written without proper literature search and analysis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C.&nbsp;Not Recommended for Support</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"color:#008000\">Reviewer 2 :</span></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">1.The problems are clearly identified and the stakeholders, although not explicitly mentioned, appear to be clinicians, as well as residents in training. 2.The unmet challenges are directly related to the proposed objectives, which are feasible, with the possible exception of &quot;identification of representative serum metabolic fingerprints to distinguish between AD patients and controls&quot;, which is still quite speculative. Alternative plans are briefly referred to, in case markers are not found or automatic methods fail. These involve, for example, the use of radiologists, which may be difficult to achieve, given time constraints (of the radiologists, as well as of the project itself). 3.The promised results (brain MRI atlas of AD for Indian patients, machine identification of lesions, identification of serum markers for AD) are ambitious and will certainly be novel if achieved. The proposed techniques to achieve these results are, however, quite standard. There is some overlap with the PIs past work, but not a very significant amount, since they have not worked specifically on the subject of the proposal. 4.The proposed output of this project is a brain MRI atlas for Indian patients, and a suite of algorithms and software for medical image analysis tasks. This output is very relevant and important. The activities are well distributed across the team members and matched to their expertise (medical image processing &amp; clinical medicine). 5.This project has a specific objective (2) devoted to training students and introducing machine learning techniques etc. in medical school curricula. This is a very positive feature, since technological and algorithmic awareness is now essential to the medical profession. 6.Team members have ample experience in the machine learning/image processing area, as well as the medical/clinical side, although neither PI has worked directly in the area of AD. Time commitments are on the low side. Suggestion: Increase time commitment of PIs, if possible. 7. The foreign mentor has been involved in computer vision and related image processing problems, rather than medical image processing, while the domestic mentor has been involved in computational intelligence algorithms. The project does not contain much detail on plans for interaction with the mentors. Suggestion: Include a mentor from the medical side. 8. Dissemination is planned through two workshops, journal papers and training and curricular changes referred to in item 5. Suggestion: Although the proposers mention curricular changes, there is no specific proposal. This could be one of the deliverables of this project proposal. However, there is no mention of industry or vendors of medical image processing equipment. Suggestion: Involvement of medical imaging equipment vendors, in order to be able to license software through them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B1. Any major mismatches in the proposed line item costs with the proposed item/work, in the format: Budget-head-Institution: Remarks. Example: &lt;Manpower-IITX: Remarks&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">None observed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B2. Any major equipment proposed for purchase that may be otherwise possible to share with others or is usable through outsourcing, without adversely affecting the work.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I am not aware of any possibilities with respect to equipment sharing or outsourcing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B3. If any proposed major equipment is costing more than Rs. 2,50,000, and sharing/outsourcing is possible but not suggested in the proposal, then (i) do you know if that equipment is already available (particularly in India) where its sharing/outsourcing may be possible, and (ii) is it absolutely necessary for the project.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">An FTIR instrument for spectral data acquisition (15 lakh) and a high-end data server (7 lakhs) are the only two items in this category and both are absolutely necessary for the project.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Good project, with high chances of producing relevant deliverables (brain MRI map for Indian patients), suite of algorithms and corresponding software for medical image processing. With regard to the second deliverable (software), I believe that it would be important to involve vendors of medical imaging equipment, since their software is usually proprietary, licensing expensive and access limited. If this is not done, the outreach of the software deliverable may be limited to academia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A.&nbsp;Recommended for Support</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"color:#008000\">Reviewer 3 :</span></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C.&nbsp;Not Recommended for Support</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"color:#008000\">Reviewer 4 :</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There is a fundamental problem in this proposal. The investigators want to integrate structural imaging (not even functional imaging or MR spectroscopy) with molecular profiling. This can&#39;t be done. Both these are information from very different levels of biological organisation. Each level in the structural hierarchy has new emergent properties, which now systems biology says cannot be understood by studying components at the lower level. So, trying to link static structural data with information obtained at the molecular level will not yield anything useful. Obtaining brain MR atlas for normal and AD will not serve any purpose in the context of the HuSim project. Biomarkers cannot be identified from static MR images. One can obtain only structural markers. Serum metabolic fingerprints are generally non-specific. Using FTIR, which gives information on chemcial functional groups in the samples will not yield fingerprints. Differences between samples cannot be picked up by FTIR. This reviewer has experience working with FTIR. NMR spectroscopy will also be nonspecific. The apectral pattern will be common to other diseases as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B1. Any major mismatches in the proposed line item costs with the proposed item/work, in the format: Budget-head-Institution: Remarks. Example: &lt;Manpower-IITX: Remarks&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">No justification has been provided by the investigators for any of the budget heads</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C.&nbsp;Not Recommended for Support</p>\r\n', '', '1'),
