>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">1.&nbsp;Rejection Quality</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">1.&nbsp;Rejection Quality</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1: The broad objective of the project are interesting and could be useful in understanding the role of basal ganglia in PD. A2: The main motivation seems to be to develop a kind of standard model of the basal-ganglia to test the effect of drugs and DBS in PD patients. This is a very ambitious goal. Absence of a specific hypothesis makes it very difficult to judge the feasibility of the project. One of the objective of the project is to find the link between alpha-syn and dopaminergic transmission. But that part of the project is very vague and it is not clear what kind of data is available to the PIs that will help the modelling and a quantitative understanding. Also in my opinion the different objectives of the project are not properly inter-linked. A3: The modelling effort is a continuation of the work done in the group of Dr. Chakravarthy. It is an interesting thought to using a behavioural task (2-bandit task) and the reinforcement learning paradigm to develop a large-scale model of the basal-ganglia. Other methods are standard. A4: The experimental data could be a useful resources. At this stage I do not expect that the computational model will be useful for predicting the effect of leva-dopa or DBS therapy &mdash; research groups in Europe and US have attempted similar modelling efforts without much success. PIs should clearly state what the key novelties of their approach that will make this project successful. A5: The PhD training program is not specified. Also there is an imbalance in the role of PIs in PhD supervision. It seems that some of the PIs even though they are responsible for an objective are not assigned as PhD supervisors (e.g. Dr. Nadkarni and Dr. Roy). A6: The PIs have ample experience in developing computer models of the basal ganglia. Similarly the PIs have expertise in the data analysis. However, I am concerned that none the PIs have any documented experience in basal-ganglia electrophysiology in rodents human fMRI/EEG in PD patients. Similarly, the low-level modelling that will link the alpha-syn to LTP/LTD appears to be a completely new work for the concerned PI. A7: There are no mentors. Given that none of the PIs have any experience with basal-ganglia electrophysiology (as there is no published work on this from any of the PIs). Therefore, I would suggest that PIs include someone with an experience in BG electrophysiology in rodents and primates. A8: Authors seems to have forgotten to fill in the outreach activities?</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B1. Any major mismatches in the proposed line item costs with the proposed item/work, in the format: Budget-head-Institution: Remarks. Example: &lt;Manpower-IITX: Remarks&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I am kind of surprised that two PIs who are responsible for two different objectives of the project are not listed as PhD supervisors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B2. Any major equipment proposed for purchase that may be otherwise possible to share with others or is usable through outsourcing, without adversely affecting the work.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I cannot comment on that.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B3. If any proposed major equipment is costing more than Rs. 2,50,000, and sharing/outsourcing is possible but not suggested in the proposal, then (i) do you know if that equipment is already available (particularly in India) where its sharing/outsourcing may be possible, and (ii) is it absolutely necessary for the project.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I cannot comment on that.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The project lacks focus and integration among the different objectives. In its current shape each objective stands alone. Some the objectives are not planned properly e.g. it is clear that basal-ganglia is a deep structure and EEG is not a good read-out of its activity. Several other information are also missing e.g. how many patients will be recruited and on what basis, what kind of animal model will be used? Furthermore, the link between the amyloid pathology and PD is not spelled out properly. Overall the project is rather poorly written and some mandatory sections are not even filled (e.g. mentors and outreach).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C.&nbsp;Not Recommended for Support</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#008000\"><strong>Reviewer 3 :</strong></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kindly indicate the list of drugs which induce dyskinesias besides L-Dopa medication</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B1. Any major mismatches in the proposed line item costs with the proposed item/work, in the format: Budget-head-Institution: Remarks. Example: &lt;Manpower-IITX: Remarks&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">-</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B2. Any major equipment proposed for purchase that may be otherwise possible to share with others or is usable through outsourcing, without adversely affecting the work.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">-</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B3. If any proposed major equipment is costing more than Rs. 2,50,000, and sharing/outsourcing is possible but not suggested in the proposal, then (i) do you know if that equipment is already available (particularly in India) where its sharing/outsourcing may be possible, and (ii) is it absolutely necessary for the project.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">-</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Can the indicated signs of impulsive behaviour in the present study be correlated to autistic behaviour</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">B.&nbsp;Borderline</p>\r\n', '', '1');
