(17, 'project478', '<h4><span style=\"color:#008000\"><strong>Reviewer 1 :</strong></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>1.&nbsp;Rejection Quality</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>2.&nbsp;Poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>1.&nbsp;Rejection Quality</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>A9. Please provide your comments and suggestions for improvement on Items A1-A8 in 8 succeeding paragraphs, numbered paragraphs.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>This proposal intend to develop a neuropsychological tool for India (diverse culture /language) . The team does not have any neuropsychologist and that lead to many serious problem for putting this grant. I quote that &quot;Apart from these advantages, the main limitation of CANTAB is its price, which is quite high and also not very much suitable for the multi-language and multi culture country like India. Lowe and Rabbit in 1998 have evaluated test/re-test correlations and practice effects for CANTAB from large groups of healthy elderly and found many of the CANTAB measures have poor test-retest reliability and modest practice effects.&quot; Cantab is a extremely powerful package development for multi language system and this research group has highlighted one paper published in 1998 and I read the paper also. From 1998 till 2015 there are 17 years passed and which is a long period and significant development have happened for various corrective measures of the package and it is almost free of cost and I have used it also. Please download the package <a href=\"http://www.cambridgecognition.com/healthcare/cantabmobile\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://www.cambridgecognition.com/healthcare/cantabmobile</a> I am wondering about the literature search for this proposal . In India, there are packages are available one from NIMHANS, one from AIIMS being applied in daily basis. One major package involving more (Nizam, aiims etc) is almost ready based on a major funding from GOVT of India. Anyone involved in this domain of research, would certainly know. Please make a google search on dementia screening in India and latest results will be available. I request to have a detailed literature search and please do not count on oldest paper to support this proposal. ======================== In this study MCI, AD, FTD and normal healthy aged persons will be studied. Every clinical study must a clear inclusion and exclusion criteria. and I quote from this grant proposal &quot;As definite Alzheimer disease diagnosis needs histopathological confirmation, we shall beusing criteria for diagnosis of probable Alzheimer disease as given by the NINCDS- ADRDA group.1 The criteria for the clinical diagnosis of probable Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease include: a) dementia established by clinical examination and documented by the Mini-Mental Test, Blessed Dementia Scale, or some similar examination, and confirmed by neuropsychological tests b) deficits in two or more areas of cognition c) progressive worsening of memory and other cognitive functions; d) no disturbance of consciousness; e) onset between ages 40 and 90, most often after age 65: and f) absence of systemic disorders or other brain diseases which could account for the progressive deficits in memory and cognition. (ii) Those cases of dementia will be excluded which correspond to 1) vascular dementia 2) secondary causes of dementia including thyroid disorders, vitamin deficiencies, infective etiology, tumours, head injury 3) seizures or gait disturbance very early in disease We shall select control Population consisting of individuals, both male and female, of more than 65 years of age having adequate care-givers who are neurologically normal for the given age.&quot; My points is that there is no inclusion and exclusion in terms of age for AD patients. Any clinical research must say who will be in and who will be excluded. Please note that any clinical study there are dropout due to various reasons. So this attrition rate must be considered. If it is not age matched, what you are comparing. There is no such plan and no thought out for FTD cases also. There must be one certificate from the clinician that he/she will give patients and N=? and tentative time frame must be mentioned. ----------------------------- Then I see this proposal wants to make new packages for resting state-fmri data analysis. Please note fantastic package is available (CONN) for resting state connectivity. It is just fantastic and there is huge scope to develop it. So starting the same stuff from scratch is far fetched. It may be noted that proposal talked about MEG/fMRI but please include what you are getting and how it will help you. Just bringing different modalities to use on a AD, MCI FTD person, is not a good idea. Please note the toolbox Fieldtrip in SPM are doing fantastic data analysis for EEG/MEG data. One can improve it if required. There must have a grand plan and literature search/analysis should help the proposal. Please have a search at national level on the same topic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>B1. Any major mismatches in the proposed line item costs with the proposed item/work, in the format: Budget-head-Institution: Remarks. Example: &lt;Manpower-IITX: Remarks&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>please make a plan where patients will come (Delhi) and imaging work to be done where, who will handle what?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>B2. Any major equipment proposed for purchase that may be otherwise possible to share with others or is usable through outsourcing, without adversely affecting the work.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>No comment</p>\r\n\r\n<p>B3. If any proposed major equipment is costing more than Rs. 2,50,000, and sharing/outsourcing is possible but not suggested in the proposal, then (i) do you know if that equipment is already available (particularly in India) where its sharing/outsourcing may be possible, and (ii) is it absolutely necessary for the project.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>no comment</p>\r\n\r\n<p>C1. Any Additional Comments:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>This proposal is based on a 17 years old paper to support the new neuropsychological tool. A clear thought out (absence of exclusion/inclusion criteria)dampen the interest. A clear plan and why so many methodology involved and what is the outcome and how it will help. In my view based on clinical research in India and oversees, 65% of this work are published and it happened due to lack of literature search/analysis. There is no plan or attempt for alternative plan. It is clearly assumed all will work as proposed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>C.&nbsp;Not Recommended for Support</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"color:#008000\"><strong>Reviewer 2 :</strong></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A2. Motivation and Objectives (Items 5, 6):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=reviewerQualification\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>A3. Technical Overview (Item 7):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=potential\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A4. Activities and Roles (Items 8-10):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=fixability\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>3.&nbsp;Bordering Acceptable</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>A5. Impact on Curricula (Item 11):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=novelty\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A6. Team (Items 12.1 and 12.2):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=technicalMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>A7. Mentors (Item 13):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=interestToCommunity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>5.&nbsp;Excellent</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A8. Outreach (Items 14, 16, 17):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=longevity\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>4.&nbsp;Good</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>C2. Your Overall Evaluation:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=grammar\">(?)</a>(shown only to chairs)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>B.&nbsp;Borderline</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"color:#008000\"><strong>Reviewer 3 :</strong></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>A1. Problem (Item 4):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://203.129.234.86/husim/hotcrp/scorehelp.php?f=overAllMerit\">(?)</a></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<