(9, '<p>1. Title:&nbsp; <strong>&quot;Rural Informatics </strong><strong>(GNR629)</strong>&rdquo; course with hands-on session at CSRE, IIT Bombay at Masters level.<br />\r\nLink: http://www.csre.iitb.ac.in/mtechProgramme.php<br />\r\nAvg. enrolment per offering: 10</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Title:&nbsp; Additional modules to <strong>&quot;Rural Informatics&quot; </strong>course for design and development of Geo-ICDT systems and Decision Support. CSRE, IIT Bombay (Masters level)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Link: http://www.csre.iitb.ac.in/mtechProgramme.php<br />\r\nAvg. enrolment per offering: 10<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Title: Developed sensor application and interoperability module for <strong>&quot;</strong><strong>Geospatial Standards, Interoperability and Knowledge Discovery (GNR629)</strong><strong> &quot;</strong><strong>,</strong> CSRE, IIT Bombay<br />\r\nLink: http://www.csre.iitb.ac.in/mtechProgramme.php<br />\r\nAvg. enrolment per offering: 10</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n4. Title: New application modules were added to<strong> &quot;</strong><strong>Geospatial Standards, Interoperability and Knowledge Discovery (GNR629)</strong><strong>&quot; </strong>Course with specialized focus on implementation of OGC standards<strong>.</strong><br />\r\nLink: http://www.csre.iitb.ac.in/mtechProgramme.php<br />\r\nAvg. enrolment per offering: 15<br />\r\n<br />\r\n5. Title: <strong>&quot;</strong><strong>Hydro-geologic characterization&quot; </strong>and<strong> &quot;Geophysical Inversion Theories&quot;</strong> in the course (CE6530 &ndash; Groundwater Modeling) taught at PG level students during:i)Jan-May 2016 and ii) Jan-Apr 2018 at IIT Hyderabad<br />\r\nAvg. enrolment per offering: 08<br />\r\n<br />\r\n6. Title: Added a chapter on <strong>&quot;</strong><strong>Root water uptake modelling using experimental and numerical framework in Groundwater Modeling (CE 6530) &quot; </strong>course taught at PG level students during Jan-May 2016 at IIT Hyderabad</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avg. enrolment per offering: 08<br />\r\n<br />\r\n7. Title: <strong>Sensors and applications in Natural resource monitoring</strong> at IIT Bombay<br />\r\nLink: http://www.csre.iitb.ac.in/mtechProgramme.php (Proposed)<br />\r\nAvg. enrolment per offering: -</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Title: Additional modules are added to &ldquo;<strong>Remote Sensing of Vegetation</strong>&rdquo; course at IIT Bombay<br />\r\nLink: http://www.csre.iitb.ac.in/mtechProgramme.php<br />\r\nAvg. enrolment per offering: 15<br />\r\n<br />\r\n9. Title: Additional modules at graduate level course in &ldquo;<strong>Groundwater Modeling</strong>&rdquo; (CE 6530) at IIT Hyderabad<br />\r\nAvg. enrolment per offering: 08<br />\r\n<br />\r\n10. Title: &ldquo;<strong>Introduced IT solutions in Plant Pathology</strong>&ldquo; courses in PDKV<br />\r\nAvg. enrolment per offering: -</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Lab: Test bed for estimation of chlorophyll fluorescence under water stressed condition for tomato plants (to be extended to Citrus)<br />\r\nLink: https://github.com/suryakant54321<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2. Lab:Test bed for usability of very low-cost sensors under different soil moisture conditions<br />\r\nLink: https://github.com/suryakant54321<br />\r\n<br />\r\n3. Development of new test bed for soil moisture estimation in collaboration with SensSprout (Japan) and GridSense<br />\r\n<cite>Link: https://sensprout.com/en/</cite><br />\r\n<br />\r\n4. Improved Telegram Bot for dissemination of sensor observations and ETo estimates (Software)<br />\r\nLink: https://github.com/suryakant54321&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Lab: Experimental test-bed for geophysical investigations at IIT Hyderabad</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Purpose: To perform surface and bore-hole ERT sections as a part of CE6530 (Groundwater Modeling) course</p>\r\n', '<p>1.Title: Additional modules and hands-on sessions are added in &ldquo;Rural Informatics&rdquo; course (IIT Bombay)<br />\r\nLink: http://www.csre.iitb.ac.in/mtechProgramme.php<br />\r\nAvg. enrolment per offering: 10<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Additional modules are added to &ldquo;Remote Sensing of Vegetation&rdquo; course (IIT Bombay)<br />\r\nLink: http://www.csre.iitb.ac.in/mtechProgramme.php<br />\r\nAvg. enrolment per offering: 10</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. New modules are added to CE6530 (Groundwater Modeling) course at IIT Hyderabad</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Lab: Hydrometeorology Lab at IIT Hyderabad was equipped ET flux tower for state-of-art hydrological research improved computational lab facilities using Hydrus 3D<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2.Lab: Improved computational lab facilities at IIT Hyderabad (Hydrus 3D)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Lab: Hydrogeology and Groundwater Lab at IIT Hyderabad was added with SAS logger (ABEM, USA) for borehole lithologic profiling</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Updated &quot;Agro-Informatics Lab&rdquo; at IIT Bombay<br />\r\nNew instruments (Revised SenseTube, SenSprout)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. High Performance Computing Facility in Geo-Semantics Lab at IIT Bombay</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Title: SenseTube - A hardware/software device to integrate sensor data, human-provided information, computational models and wireless communications to manage crop resources.<br />\r\nRegistration date: &nbsp;Proposed<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2. Title: Hydrology &amp; Groundwater Consulting: A service for detecting and estimating the size of ground water resources in hard rock aquifers<br />\r\nof India.<br />\r\nRegistration date: Proposed</p>\r\n', '<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:726px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:167px; width:49px\">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:167px; width:676px\">\r\n			<p>1. Title: SenseTube:&nbsp; A Syntactically Standardized Web Enabled Wireless&nbsp;&nbsp; Sensor&nbsp;&nbsp; Network System for Precision Agriculture Applications (An interoperable on-site processing and analysis platform for WSN)<br />\r\n			Application Number: 2236/MUM/2015<br />\r\n			Filing Date: 10/06/2015<br />\r\n			Published Date: 16/12/2016</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>2. Title: e-Citrus:&nbsp; A Prototype Crowd Sourcing System for Agricultural Advisory Services&nbsp;&nbsp; in&nbsp; Pest&nbsp; and Disease Management<br />\r\n			Application Number: PAT/CR/JA-1/13-14<br />\r\n			Filing Date:&nbsp; Oct 29, 2013</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:726px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:176px; width:676px\">\r\n			<p>1. Title: Winter School on &ldquo;Geographical-Information, Communication and Dissemination Technologies in Water Resources&rdquo; at IIT Hyderabad<br />\r\n			Date: 6-8th Jan 2015<br />\r\n			Participants: 30 participants from academia and industry<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			2. Title: ITRA-Water closure workshop, IIT Hyderabad<br />\r\n			Date: 10-11 Jul 2017<br />\r\n			Participants: ~ 125:<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			3. Title: ITRA-Water closure workshop, IIT Bombay<br />\r\n			Date: 11-12 Jan 2016<br />\r\n			Participants: ~ 125:</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '<p>1. Title: Short course on &lsquo;Groundwater Modeling through Fractured Geologic Media&rsquo; (In collaboration with Prof. Walter A Illman, University of Waterloo Canada who was the main instructor to the course)<br />\r\nDate :&nbsp; 27 June &ndash; 08 July, 2016<br />\r\nParticipants: 30</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Title: Pre-Workshop Tutorial IoT in Agriculture, ITRA Evaluation Workshop IITB<br />\r\nDate: 11/01/2016<br />\r\nParticipants: 75</p>\r\n', '<p>0</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Title: Five days workshop on &lsquo;Citrus Production Technology&#39; at KrishakBhawan, Dr. PDKV, Akola for the scientists of SAU&rsquo;s and Agriculture Officers of State Agricultural Department of Vidarbha region<br />\r\nDate: 15-19 March 2016<br />\r\nParticipants: 50<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2. Title: Workshop on &lsquo;Citrus crop management&rsquo;, at PDKV Akola<br />\r\nDate: 15-19 March 2016<br />\r\nParticipants: 35<br />\r\n<br />\r\n3. Title: National Seminar on &ldquo;Geo-informatics Applications in Natural Resources Management&rdquo;, 18-19 March, 2016 at NIRD&amp;PR, Hyderabad</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date: 18-19 March 2016<br />\r\nParticipants: 40<br />\r\n<br />\r\n4. Title: Session on IoT (Infinity of Things) in IITB Techfest 2016 demonstrating technologies developed as part of this project</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date: 23-24 December 2016<br />\r\nParticipants: 50</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Title: Hands-on session on IoT and its applications (design to deployment) for faculty and students in Mumbai University<br />\r\nYear:&nbsp; 4-5th January 2016</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants: 60 (including students and college teachers)</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Industry: <strong>Datamatrix Systems</strong><br />\r\nCollaboration Area: Remote monitoring of pump operations, monitor energy &amp; water use with ground water level monitoring and performance analysis</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Industry: <strong>Tata Consultancy Services &ndash; Innovation Labs</strong><br />\r\nCollaboration Area: mKRISHI initiative from TCS Innovation labs provided personalized and integrated services in local language (Marathi) to farmers on their mobile phones.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. &nbsp;Industry: <strong>Vassar Labs, Andhra Pradesh &ndash; </strong>A startup company that works on real-time DSS in agriculture</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Collaboration Area: Real time DSS support</p>\r\n', '<p>0</p>\r\n', '<p>1. NGO: Center for sustainable agriculture, Tarnaka, Secunderbad (Collaboration initiated)<br />\r\nCollaboration Area: Selection of experimental plots, resilient</p>\r\n', '<p>1. International Organization:&nbsp; SenSprout and University of Tokyo<br />\r\nCollaboration Area: Soil Moisture Sensing<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2. International Organization:<strong> </strong>Collaboration with INRA France, University of Tokyo, NARO Japan, National Universities of Vietnam and Thailand in a consortium based Project under the regional program &lsquo;STIC - Asia (ICT ASIA)&rsquo; on &lsquo;BD-Farm:<strong> </strong><br />\r\nCollaboration Area:<strong> </strong>Big Data Management and Analytics for Agriculture&rsquo; to strengthen high-level scientific cooperation through mobility and networking in the Grand Challenge area of Big Data in Agriculture and research network development on digital agriculture.<strong> </strong></p>\r\n', '<p>1. Organization: <strong>Maharashtra Orange Growers Association (MOGA)</strong><br />\r\nCollaboration Area: Actively involved in providing testbeds for experiments, facilitation, and maintenance of prototypes and conducting farmers meet for disseminating the outcomes of the research.</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Solution: e-Citrus:&nbsp; A Prototype Crowd Sourcing System for Agricultural Advisory Services&nbsp;&nbsp; in&nbsp; Pest&nbsp; and Disease Management<br />\r\nProvided to: Farmers and orange growers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. SenseTube: Interoperable agro-meteorological observation and analysis platform for precision agriculture</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Groundwater Modeling solutions with BAIF (IITH)</p>\r\n', '<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:726px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:205px; width:49px\">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:205px; width:676px\">\r\n			<p>1. Service: Services developed during the project are linked with user friendly interface to interact with the system. Apart from this, information generated through systems can be available to the end users using multiple platforms such as WhatsApp group (IWC Water Group), Twitter handle (KrishiSense) and through messages sent to registered farmers,<br />\r\n			Offered to: Farmers and anyone want the related information</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><br />\r\n			2. Service: mKRISHI &ndash; Rural Participatory Sensing (RuPS) platform<br />\r\n			Offered to: Farmers, Local resource persons, Field officers<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			3. Developed Telegram based mobile Sensor Observation Service and Sensor Event Notification for agro-meteorological data dissemination</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Offered to: Farmers, Local resource persons, Field officers</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>4. Automatic Weather Station: Regular weather information dissemination for agricultural practices and management.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '<p>0</p>\r\n', '<p>0</p>\r\n', '<p>1. <a href=\"https://www.journals.elsevier.com/geoderma-regional/editorial-board\">Board: Geoderma Regional (Elsevier)- Dr. J. Adinarayana&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. <a href=\"http://www.cigr.org/Governance/technical-sections-7.php\">Board: CIGR-Section VII/IT in Agriculture- Dr. J. Adinarayana&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. <a href=\"http://Link: http://www.afita.org/\">Board: AFITA(full), President &ndash; Dr. J. Adinarayana</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Founding Board member for CUAHSI, a consortium of over 110 universities for the advancement of hydrologic science- Dr. Praveen Kumar</p>\r\n', 9, '2018-05-22 01:29:54', 'enables', '5'),
