(11, '<p>1. Title: Tailor made Hydrologic Model at BITS Pilani Hyderabad- Three modules, namely, Runoff, Routing and Water quality blocks have completed and other modules are in the process of refining.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is not part of any course. However, it is the one of the research objective of V. Swathi, Ph.D Student at BITS Pilani Hyderabad Campus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Urban Hydrology Course has been approved by the senate at BITS Hyderabad</p>\r\n\r\n<p>CE F422: Urban Hydrology</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contents: Background of urban hydrology; urban flooding; description of hydrological and planning models such as SWMM, HEC-HMS, HEC-RAS, EPANET, WEAP, SWAT; urban flood forecasting and mitigation strategies; Urban flood planning in changing climate; description of general circulation models and downscaling approaches; Management of Syphonic rainwater systems and detention facilities; sustainable urban drainage systems (SUDS);case studies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Course is yet to offer</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. New Modules Introduced&nbsp; in the BITS Hyderabad are: SWMM, HEC-HMS, HEC-RAS, EPANET, WEAP, SWAT; urban flood forecasting and mitigation strategies; Urban flood planning in changing climate; description of&nbsp; general circulation models and downscaling approaches</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Link Not Applicable.</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Lab: A laboratory experimental set up created in Hydraulics laboratory at IISc, which will implement flow sensors from CDAC for different flow conditions</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Lab: Sensor Network Based Cyber Physical Infrastructure for Continuous Monitoring of Water Distribution Networks is built in the IISc laboratory to study the flow behavior as well as the quality degradation in the water network.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This set up is built with the support from RBCCPS and IBM.</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Title: Existing course, &ldquo;Urban Hydrology&rdquo; enhanced to include: (a) climate change impacts, (b) rainfall disaggregation and (c) flood management issues at IISc Bangalore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Avg. enrolment per offering: 10</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. New modules on simulation of urban drainage system and design of urban drainage design are included in the Hydraulic and Hydrologic Design Laboratory Course of M. Tech. program in Water Resources Engineering at NITW</p>\r\n\r\n<p>https://nitw.ac.in/media/Scheme&amp;Syllabus-2014/M.Tech-WRE-Syllabus.pdf</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. A new module of urban storm water modeling using SWMM included in Hydraulic and Hydrologic Design Lab course of M. Tech, Water Resources Engineering Programing NITW.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>https://nitw.ac.in/media/Scheme&amp;Syllabus-2014/M.Tech-WRE-Syllabus.pdf</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. New modules on simulation of urban drainage system and design of urban drainage design are included in the Hydraulic and Hydrologic Design Laboratory Course of M. Tech program in Water Resources Engineering at NITW</p>\r\n\r\n<p>https://nitw.ac.in/media/Scheme&amp;Syllabus-2014/M.Tech-WRE-Syllabus.pdf</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Lab:&nbsp; Scaled model of open channel is built in the Hydraulics Laboratory of IISc for studying the urban flooding effects. The setup is fully instrumented to understand the dynamics of the water flow due to various changes in the pathway. A rigorous comparison of the experimental and CFD analysis is done to understand the behavior of clogging and gate operation on floods.</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Title: FLOODLITE<br />\r\nRegistration date: Not yet registered</p>\r\n', '<p>0</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Title: Monsoon School on Urban Floods at IISc Bangalore</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Date: Aug 4 &ndash;9 , 2014</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Participants: 35</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Title: Monsoon school on urban flood at IISc Bangalore</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Date: 24th to 29th August2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Participants: 50</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3, Title: Winter School on Urban Flood Modeling at 