nts: 96</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Workshop-cum-Training Program on Urban Flood Management: Technology Driven Solutions, at BITS-Pilani, Hyderabad Campus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date : March 3-4, 2017</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants: 65</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Title: A tutorial was conducted at the IISc covering the topics flood plain mapping in HEC GeoRAS, HEC RAS, SWMM and development of IDF relationships</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date : May 6, 8, 9 and 11, 2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants: 30</p>\r\n', '<p>0</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Title: Workshop on Integrated Urban Flood Management for Hyderabad: Technology Driven Solutions at BITS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date:&nbsp; 31 October 2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants: 27</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Title: Training program on Urban Flood Management: Technology Driven Solutions at BITS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date: 20-21 November 2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants: 41</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. 3-day training program on Integrated 1D and 2D Urban Flood Modelling using MIKE Urban and MIKE Flood (The training was given by Mr. Prashanth from DHI (India))</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date: 11-13 July, 2016</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants:15</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. A workshop was arranged under the leadership of Director KSNDMC, BBMP commissioner, and National Disaster Relief team for 100 BBMP officials, including BBMP Zonal officers, ward level officers and field level officers. The training and insight was given to the officials to better implement the Early warning and forecast information given by KSNDMC</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date: 8th June 2016</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants: 50</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. A three day training program on integrated 1D 2D urban flood modelling using MIKE Flood at NIT Warangal</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date: July 11-13, 2016</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants: 10</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. A national seminar on Climate Change Adaptation &ndash; Issues and Challenges CCAIC-2016 was organized at Civil Engineering Department, Faculty of Tech &amp; Engg, MSU Baroda</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date: 12th December 2016</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants- 96</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. A workshop on &ldquo;Integrated Urban Flood Management: Technology Driven Solutions&rdquo; was held at IISc Bangalore</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date: September 20th, 2016</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants: 30</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Workshop-cum-Training Program on Urban Flood Management: Technology Driven Solutions, during at BITS-Pilani, Hyderabad Campus (65 participants).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date: March 3-4, 2017</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants: 65</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. A webinar training program was conducted by IISc to train KSNDMC, BITS Pilani Hyderabad and NIT Warangal on floodplain mapping using the software like SWMM, ArcGIS and inp.PINS Extension.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Date: 28th April 2016</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants: 12</p>\r\n', '<p>0</p>\r\n', '<p>0</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Deptt/Ministry: A MoU signed between KSNDMC and IISc which will facilitate IISc to obtain high frequency rainfall data from KSNDMC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Collaboration Area: Get near real time rainfall data; developing ,calibrating and validating the hydrological model; dissemination of the output; train the scientific personnel of KSNDMC with various advanced methods</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. IISc has signed MOU with BBMP, Karnataka.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Collaboration Area: model development through measurement of real time floods; Share all other data relevant; Provide infrastructure support where possible for conducting field studies; upgrade the model periodically</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Deptt/Ministry: MOU signed between NIT Warangal and&nbsp; Greater Hyderabad Municipal Corporation (GHMC) with &nbsp;BITS Hyderabad as a partner for data procuring and project discussion</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Collaboration Area: Storm water network design (broad area: Water Resources Department) data sharing; developing ,calibrating and validating the hydrological model; dissemination of the output; train the scientific personnel of KSNDMC with various advanced methods</p>\r\n', '<p>0</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Development of an Educational Portal (A Collaborative Venture between UNESCO, IISc, And PURDUE)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Link: <a href=\"https://urbandrought.org/research/downscaling.html\">https://urbandrought.org/research/downscaling.html</a></p>\r\n', '<p>1. Organization: Centre for Atmospheric and Oceanic Sciences (CAOS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Collaboration Area: Installion of Automatic Weather Station (AWS) inside campus, June 2015</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Organization: Indian Institute of Technology, Bombay</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Collaboration Area: Design of an Expert System for Flood forecasting and management for the city of Chennai</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Technology: Hydrological modelling</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Trasferred to: Karnataka State Natural Disaster Monitoring Center (KSNDMC)</p>\r\n', '<p>1.Stake holders like municipal corporations and urban development authorities taken into confidence and involved in implementation of results</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Installation of 8 new rain gauge stations at Vadodara done, by Vadodara Municipal Corporation &ndash;as a result of learning from KSNDMC through MS University</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Inter-linking of 8 ponds with gated storm water drains initiated by Vadodara Municipal SevaSadan for management of flood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Bangalore Development Authority (BDA) is currently in engagement with IISc for the storm water drainage component of Vision 2030.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. A rapid assessment report on Chennai Floods 2015 is published and available</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Link- <a href=\"http://www.icwar.iisc.ernet.in/chennai-floods-2015/\">http://www.icwar.iisc.ernet.in/chennai-floods-2015/</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. IDF relationships developed for Hyderabad city</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Greater Hyderabad Municipal Corporation (GHMC)</p>\r\n', '<p