(1, 'project451', 2, 'Monica Sundd', '', '', '', 'NA', 'Authors plan to set up a crystallography lab in the first year. This may take quite a bit of time of the project.', 'A recent study (2016) shows that \"Î³-Secretase Activating Protein (GSAP) does not specifically affect the Î³-Secretase processing of APP\". Rather than specifically regulating Î³-secretase cleavage of APP, GSAP also regulated the levels of sAPPÎ², the ectodomain shedded by the Î²-secretase processing of APP. The role of GSAP in alzheimers as a drug target is being questioned. Authors have not provided a complete picture of the role of GSAP in APP processing. Another recent study has stated that GSAP is itself regulated by caspase-3, which appears to ', 'The project has novelty if we look at the literature 4 years back. However, recent developments have questioned the role of GSAP in APP processing, as it is associated with the release of the cytoplasmic part as well.', 'One aspect of the project is to solve the structure of GSAP, and use in silico studies using insilico inhibitors. The other part is to use fluid flow simulations to cross brain barrier. Another issue is that authors are using imatinib as an inhibitor of GSAP, while recent reports show that the drug does not have any effect on GSAP.', ' Authors seem confused what they plan to do. They propose crystallography, along with NMR and then also insilico structure generation. There is no preliminary data available with the authors.', '', '', '', 'Its not worth funding 80 lakh for a project on a protein that is already being questioned in the alzheimers community.', '', '', '', 'The protein chosen as a drug target is worrisome. Recently, over expression of GSAP has been shown to have no effect on APP production or abeta processing. A number of studies have questioned the role of this protein (GSAP) in APP processing. One study states that it does not specifically regulate GSAP, but also regulates the levels of sAPPÎ², the ectodomain shedded by the Î²-secretase processing of APP, and hence may not turn out to be a good target. The role of GSAP in alzheimers as a drug target is also being questioned. In the light of these new', 'YES', 'YES', 'YES', 'NA', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'YES', 'YES', 'YES', 'NO', 'NO', 'YES', '', 'NO', '', '', '', '0000-00-00'),
