(3, 'project461', 5, 'Soumen Basak', 'The research problem has been clearly described, but how this will positively contribute towards a solution remains unclear.', 'The hypothesis behind the proposal appeared only moderately strong. It is uncertain if GRN analyses will lead to the identification of cause or consequence of amyloid formation in T2D.  The basic premise underlying the second objective is also only moderately strong.', 'The proposal consists of two seemingly unrelated goals.  \r\nFor the first part related to RNA/gene analyses: The PI did not define the time points for control and amylin-expressing cells.  It is truly puzzling, how would to define \"0 hour\" for amylin-expressing cell-liine.  How does one conduct time-point experiments in control cells? What will be used for stimulation and why?  Note, S-systems require temporal gene-expression profiles, and it is unclear how the data set will be generated to feed into the simulator.  More so, validation of GRN-based i', 'NA', 'This reviewer does not believe that validation of insights gained from GRN-data analyses in patient sample is feasible within the three years time periods. ', '', 'The GRN-based and related analyses are conduced all over the world.  The important aspect of this grant is to apply those in understanding the function of pro-aggregatory proteins in T2D.  But poorly laid out work plan does not convince of its success. ', 'The program consists of two seemingly unrelated objectives. \r\nSecond goal is clearly not related to the basic tenant of investigating pro-aggregatory proteins, as emphasised in the original RFP. ', 'This reviewer does not believe that validation of insights gained from GRN-data analyses in patient sample is feasible within the three years time periods. ', 'A lack of information of time-points for RNA collection, no of experimental replicates, no of patient samples to be analysed obstructed a favourable decision on this matter.', 'A lack of information of time-point