(76, 'project467', 6, 'Lipi Thukral', 'The expected outcomes are still not clear. While the study has been re-defined, the specifics of the execution are not listed properly.', 'The hypothesis has been roughly outlined by putting together as application of neural nanonetworks for AD treatment. This along with other objectives aim to provide a mobile app based system for clinicians (how these are interconnected and what is the hypothesis is unknown).', 'Unfortunately, this aspect has been massively overlooked. While the individual objectives stated from Pg 17-19 are sound when considered in isolation, the synergy of the proposal in totality is non-specific. ', 'NA', 'The concern about feasibility about the project was unanimously raised by all previous 4 reviewers. However the response to the same has been the following: \"@Reviewer 1, @Reviewer 2, @Reviewer3, and @Reviewer 4: Since the objectives are\r\nclearly defined in the revised proposal, it is quite feasible that objective deliverables can\r\nbe made.\" In due of this, the reviewer is thoroughly confused if the question was even answered.', 'The authors have explained the previous comments by reviewers', 'The novelty is less', 'The redefined part of the work has been modified  a) by adding a new collaborator b) to provide ICT based alternative solutions amongst others. However the reviewer is unable to obtain clarity on existing work. The interdisciplinary nature of the work needs requires extensive back-and-forth cross talk between all partners, which is most non-coherant.', 'not feasible. ', 'The authors have put the rebuttal that the budget was questioned earlier. The same has not been thoroughly revised.', 'The authors have put the rebuttal that the budget was questioned earlier. The same has not been thoroughly revised.', 'They have reduced the intake.', 'the same as above', 'the same as above', 'the same as above', '', 'Overall the project cannot be supported due to a) lack of coherance within different modules b) how different expertise is linked to each is unknown, and c) lastly the outcomes still remain unclear. ', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'NA', 'NO', 'YES', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'YES', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', '', 'NO', 'The proposed study does not incorporate exact suggestions made by the reviewers. ', 'NO', 'yes', '0000-00-00'),
(77, 'project467', 11, 'Siddhartha kundu', '', '', '', 'NA', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Despite the domain expertise of all the PIs, the proposal itself does not possess the clarity sought by the previous and this reviewer(s). Indeed, the specific problem that is to be addressed by the PIs remains elusive and confusing in spite of the multiple rounds of revisions and discussions.    ', '', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'NA', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'YES', 'NO', 'YES', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', '', 'NO', '', 'NO', 'yes', '0000-00-00'),
(78, 'project457', 11, 'Siddhartha kundu', '', '', 'There are several sub-objectives which seem coherent with the overall proposal, but are difficult to accomplish all at once and within the time frame ITRA desires.  ', 'NA', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'The proposal is well written and relevant. However, a major concern of this reviewer is that the role of IT has been reduced to mere analytics. There are no simulations, no hypotheses, and no predictions. \r\n\r\nThe proposal is in the words of the PIs a \"data generating\" exercise, which despite its importance seems to be in conflict with the concept of interdisciplinary and equal contributory work. There are several proposals/ manuscripts which the PIs could have consulted for achieving this integration. \r\n\r\nYet, another concern of this reviewer was the feasibility of completing the objectives of the proposal in the defined time frame, i.e., 2018.', 'Not in the present form.', 'YES', 'NO', 'NO', 'NA', 'NO', 'NO', 'YES', 'YES', 'NO', 'YES', 'YES', 'YES', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', '', 'NO', '', 'NO', 'yes', '0000-00-00'),
(80, 'project449', 11, 'Siddhartha kundu', '', '', '', 'NA', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Despite the domain expertise of all the PIs, the proposal itself does not possess the clarity sought by the previous and this reviewer(s). \r\nIndeed, the specific problem that is to be addressed by the PIs remains elusive and confusing despite  the multiple rounds of revisions and discussions. Whilst, the sub-proposals are well written and seemingly coherent, the work is still too diverse and lacks focus. It is difficult to fathom the nature of the actual deliverables that the PIs would accomplish in the duration proposed.  There is also a large body of preliminary work not directly related to the proposal.  \r\n', 'Not in the current form.', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'NA', 'NO', 'YES', 'YES', 'YES', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', 'NO', '', 'NO', '', 'NO', 'yes', '0000-00-00'),
