(38, 'ipsm', '2018-06-13 15:30:11', '<p>There are two types of Student Awards:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. </strong><strong>PhD</strong><strong> Research Award</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>To help continuously enhance the quality of PhD research, ITRA will recognize good work done by PhD students annually.<br />\r\nThe research performance of each student will be evaluated and assigned a performance grade at the end of eachyear, by a panel comprising mainly of technical experts.<br />\r\nAwards will be given annually.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Award worthy work will be assigned one of two levels &ndash; Exemplary and Outstanding.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The award will consist of:<br />\r\nFor Exemplary Performance:2 L<br />\r\nFor Outstanding Level: 1 L</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. </strong><strong>PhD</strong><strong> Dissertation Award</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>To recognize high quality of PhD thesis of students in ITRA teams, in which the individual contributions made in different parts have high coherence and integrative value.<br />\r\nPhD theses will be evaluated for quality and impact and those theses meeting a quality threshold will be given the award. This award will be given annually.<br />\r\nThe award will consist of a citation and a gold plated medal.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>General Guidelines</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>1. All awards are planned to be given at the end of a year, based on the performance during the year, applicable to only the following, one year.<br />\r\n2. The awards will be given to individual Students of ITRA Institutions.<br />\r\n3. The awards are based on self-competition, i.e., making noteworthy leaps in capabilities, and not based on performing better than others. Whether an award is even given in a specific year would depend on whether anyone has made award-worthy progress with respect to the award criteria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'STUDENT AWARDS', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2018-06-13 15:45:36', '', 'general', 3),
(39, 'ipsm', '2018-06-13 15:30:37', '<p>Faculty leadership is central to the success of the ITRA projects. Team awards are aimed at recognizing the leadership of PIs, Co-PIs and other senior personnel for the collaborative achievements made by their teams.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are four types of Team Award Grants:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Foresight Award Grant</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>To encourage potential ITRA teams to be ambitious and come up with bold new ideas as a part of planning for ITRA project activities, particularly for addressing India specific problems. Accordingly, ITRA project proposals will be recognized for innovative, out-of-the-box content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The award will consist of a grant in the amount of Rs. 10 L</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Team Achievement Award Grant</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>To recognizeperformance of an ITRA team with respect to each of the four ITRA quality metrics (Research, Impact on Curriculum, Societal Sensitivity Development and Outreach)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The award will be in three categories, each for award worthy performance with respectto the following groupings of ITRA performance metrics:<br />\r\n(i) Research,<br />\r\n(ii) Curricular Impact, and<br />\r\n(iii) Societal Sensitivity Development and Outreach(combined).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Award worthy work will be assigned one of two levels &ndash; Exemplary and Outstanding.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The award will consist of a grant, in the amount of:<br />\r\nFor Exemplary Level:20 L<br />\r\nFor Outstanding Level:10 L</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Partnership Award Grant</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>To recognize a particularly important aspect of ITRA architecture &ndash; Partnering Institutions (PINs) in a pyralet advancing their quality with the help of their Lead Institution (LIN). It highlights the high level of importance ITRA associates with inter-institutional collaboration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Award worthy work will be assigned one of two levels &ndash; Exemplary and Outstanding.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The award will consist of a grant, in the amount of:<br />\r\nFor Exemplary level: 6 L (i.e., 3 L/institution)<br />\r\nFor Outstanding level: 3L (i.e., 1.5 L/institution)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Interdisciplinary Collaboration Award Grant</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>To recognizecross-fertilization achievementsbetween IT institutions and X (domain specific) institutions in a team, leading to major interdisciplinary advances in IT-in-X research projects.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The award will have 2 levels &ndash; Exemplary and Outstanding.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The award will consist of a grant, in the amount of:<br />\r\nFor Exemplary level: 6 L (i.e., 3 L/institution)<br />\r\nFor Outstanding level: 3L (i.e., 1.5 L/institution)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>Each award will be in the form of a grant to the team. The recipient team will submit a brief statement of work along with a budget for the award amount. The budget will be flexible in that it could be used for any category of expense, e.g., to attend a different type of conference, invite experts, hire extra students for possible new work, etc., as needed. Any use of the award grant money on large equipment or international travel by the researchers will be acceptable, but it will be subject to the pertinent ITRA policies, and therefore, will require prior ITRA approval.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>General Guidelines</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>1. All awards are planned to be given at the end of a year, based on the performance during the year, applicable to only the following, one year.<br />\r\n2. The awards will be given to an entire team of ITRA Institutions.<br />\r\n3. The awards are based on self-competition, i.e., making noteworthy leaps in capabilities, and not based on performing better than others. Whether an award is even given in a specific year would depend on whether anyone has made award-worthy progress with respect to the award criteria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The extent of progress is judged from quantitative measurements of performance with respect to the four ITRA metrics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'TEAM AWARD GRANTS', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2018-06-13 15:44:22', '', 'general', 2);
INSERT INTO `web_testimonial` (`id`, `content`, `name`, `img`, `ondate`, `extra`) VALUES
(1, '<p><q>Bringing people from different institutes, different culture working together during and even after the end of the projects is a positive outcome of ITRA.</q></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Dr. Nani Bhowmik, Illinois State Water Survey, USA', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Nani-Bhowmik.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:19:47', 'active'),
(2, '<p>The work done by&nbsp;<em>ITRA-Water</em>&nbsp;teams is important for the nation as far as the water sector is concerned and we need to take this forward, the intensity of it has to be increased, its application to the fields has to be enhanced.&nbsp;ITRA&rsquo;s evaluation process increases the quality of the work going on based on the interactions between the teams and the review panel for mid-term course correction.&nbsp;We have to create a sustainable community, which can sustain on its own.</p>\r\n', 'Prof. Vinod Tare, IIT Kanpur', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Vinod-Tare.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:23:04', 'active'),
(3, '<p>The rigorous review process has helped us improve research quality a lot. Our project has 6 papers in published in tier one conferences which is an excellent outcome for Indian standards.</p>\r\n', 'Dr. Pushpendra Singh, IIIT Delhi', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Puspendra-Singh.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:40:52', 'active'),
(4, '<p>I think ITRA projects are directly relevant to the Indian context,&nbsp;not necessarily as products that people can use, but as steps&nbsp;toward these products, which implies growth.</p>\r\n', 'Prof. Thomas O Binford, Read-Ink Technologies Pvt. Ltd., Bangalore', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Thomas-Binford.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:41:47', 'active'),
(5, '<p>The approach to research that ITRA is fostering is going to have significant impact. Most exciting is the Idea of getting researchers together internationally and researchers, student in India, to address challenging problems from very diverse backgrounds.&nbsp;The cross institutional collaboration that has happened, the enthusiasm of the students is very fortunate.&nbsp;The legacy of ITRA is here to stay.</p>\r\n', 'Prof. Praveen Kumar, UIUC, USA', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Praveen-Kumar.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:43:07', 'active'),
(6, '<p>ITRA is very helpful for a way to grow along with our students, to solve societal problems. It is a real collaborative project which brings different communities, people and stakeholders along with end users to work together to address significant societal problems. The way ITRA reviewed the individual proposals and then later on collated and combined these proposals to really address a problem is marvelous. The review meetings have helped us a lot to think innovatively and come up with new ideas.<!-- ITRA is very critically trying to translate what we are able to do and what we can do and translate it into a product that can be applied at the field level, which is very unique.--></p>\r\n', 'Dr. K.B.V.N. Phanindra, IIT Hyderabad', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/phanindra.jpg', '2018-04-23 14:36:43', 'active'),
(7, '<p>Very nice concept. ITRA gave us the opportunity to work not only with Indian colleagues but also to interact with the international mentors at regular intervals. Overall a good community in terms of interaction.</p>\r\n', 'Prof. N.S. Raghuwanshi, IIT Kharagpur', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/N.S.-Raghuwanshi.png', '2018-03-12 12:44:31', 'active'),
(8, '<p>ITRA is ambitious in trying to solve many problems with one effort such as innovatively solving real world problems through research, and to make research teams with one renowned institution and with other institutions that are not that renowned today with the expectation that these institutions will one day be able to become a lead institution. As mentioned, it is very ambitious and significant progress has been made.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Prof. Huzur Saran, IIT DelhiÂ ', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Huzur-Saran.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:47:42', 'active'),
(9, '<p>In principle ITRA&rsquo;s evaluation process is very good, it&rsquo;s not about routine presentation, it&rsquo;s about brainstorming in which anyone can ask their queries, it&rsquo;s more like sharing of information and problem solving.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Prof. Nayan Sharma, IIT Roorkee', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Nayan-Sharma.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:48:32', 'active'),
(10, '<p>The focus on real world impact as well as research excellence which is extremely good and that is what we need to ensure that we get tangible output from these research programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Dr. Manish Gupta, Xerox, Bangalore', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Manish-Gupta.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:49:10', 'active'),
(11, '<p>ITRA provided us one of the best platform to work together with different institutes and Govt. agencies and enjoy working together as a team to complete our project which is our first and foremost achievement as a group, apart from the technical outputs. This has most benefited the research students for collaboration with different institutes whose credit goes to ITRA. Flexibility in terms of funding corresponding to travel of students for research is very different and encouraging as compared to other funding agencies. It has been a very enjoyable experience working with such wonderful colleagues and students. <!-- ITRA has tremendous opportunities in the coming years especially in widening the scope and reaching out to different fields and providing leadership not only in India but also in the surrounding countries. --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Prof. P.P.Mujumdar, IISc Bangalore', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/P.P.Mujumdar.jpg', '2018-04-23 14:34:54', 'active'),
(12, '<p>It&rsquo;s an excellent model to follow, I personally have benefited from this model, but it does have it&rsquo;s challenges.</p>\r\n', 'Dr. Sergey Gorinski, IMDEA Networks, Spain', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Sergey-Gorinsky.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:51:13', 'active'),
(13, '<p>ITRA offers a good combination of institutional and corporate research, the corporate research brings in the necessary experience for research management and it&rsquo;s a great encouragement for the new professors to bring in industrialized research.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Dr. Satish Rath, Xerox, Bangalore', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Satish-Rath.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:51:58', 'active'),
(14, '<p>I think ITRA is a very good experiment in the context of Indian academia, it tries to build the essential &lsquo;habits&rsquo; of well performing academic teams.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Dr. Shiv Kalyanraman, IBM, Bangalore', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Shiv-Kalyanraman.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:52:33', 'active'),
(15, '<p>ITRA is unique and it somehow essentially dismantles the long existing hierarchical research structure and it brings very senior professors and then at the same time the ones who have just joined the academia as young students, which is a phenomenal contribution of ITRA in changing the mindset of people about higher education. ITRA has brought individuals, stakeholders together in one family for role to play in a collective idea of development that essentially leverages the power of information technology and one of the most scarce resources in the world i.e. Water.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Dr. Bhanu Neupane, UNESCO, Paris', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Bhanu-Neupane.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:54:13', 'active'),
(16, '<p>ITRA is one of the innovative programme by MeitY.&nbsp;This project is not only confined to domestic institutes, it also has an International component to it, for mentoring and guidance in achieving the results.&nbsp;ITRA need to really take this experience to a different level by bringing additional funding and to involve more number of institutes and more number of research areas, not confined to only Mobile and Water domains, it should have a integration and sustainability aspects for societal impact in great way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Dr. Ajay Pradhan, C2S2, New Delhi', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Ajay-Pradhan.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:54:52', 'active'),
(17, '<p>ITRA has forced us to think from a multiplicity of viewpoints and asked hard questions about very relevant 21st century engineering problems.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Dr.Â Gaurav Raina, IIT Madras', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Gaurav-Raina.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:55:29', 'active'),
(18, '<p>The ITRA architecture is the best I have seen when it comes to project sanctions and evaluations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Dr. Manish Shrivastava, IIIT Hyderabad', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Manish-Shrivastava.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:56:05', 'active'),
(19, '<p>I would rate the ITRA initiative very highly on three aspects. Firstly, it is one of the very few programmes, especially in India, that brings collaboration of the top tier institutions with the upcoming institutions, providing opportunity for students to interact with the big names in their domains, which really doesn&rsquo;t exist in any other project.&nbsp;The second point I would like to highlight is pushing the research to not being limited on paper or have top level publications but also to have societal impact.&nbsp;Thirdly, bringing in international experts help the team benchmark themselves internationally rather than bench-marking them nationally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Dr. Archan Misra, SMU, Singapore', 'https://itra.medialabasia.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Archan-Misra.jpg', '2018-03-12 12:56:44', 'active');
